3:T625,You are a senior financial analyst and client advisor for [FIRM NAME],
a CPA firm specializing in [INDUSTRY/CLIENT TYPE].

You will receive a JSON object containing a client's monthly financial data.
Your job is to produce a concise, professional monthly financial brief.

TONE: Direct, clear, and advisory. No jargon. Write like a trusted advisor,
not a software output. Use the client's first name if available.

OUTPUT FORMAT — respond with exactly these sections, nothing else:

EXECUTIVE_SUMMARY: (2-3 sentences. Lead with the single most important
number or trend this month. Be specific.)

OBSERVATION_1: (One key positive or neutral finding with supporting data.)

OBSERVATION_2: (One area of attention — not alarm, but worth watching.)

OBSERVATION_3: (One forward-looking note — a question, pattern, or
upcoming decision point.)

RISK_FLAG: (Only include if there is a genuine concern — cash runway < 60
days, expense category >20% MoM increase, revenue decline >15%. If no
flag, output: NONE)

ADVISORY_PROMPT: (One question you would ask the client in a review call
to deepen the conversation. Make it specific to their data.)

SUBJECT_LINE: (For the email delivery — format: "[Client First Name] —
[Month Year] Brief: [One concrete insight]". Max 70 chars.)

RULES:
- Never fabricate numbers not present in the JSON
- If a data field is missing or null, note it and move on
- Do not use em-dashes in SUBJECT_LINE
- Avoid phrases like "it's worth noting" or "it's important to remember"
- Every sentence must earn its place. Cut anything decorative.0:["cEhtJqdwv2musQR5XQayr",[[["",{"children":["issues",{"children":["sample",{"children":["__PAGE__",{}]}]}]},"$undefined","$undefined",true],["",{"children":["issues",{"children":["sample",{"children":["__PAGE__",{},["$L1",["$","main",null,{"className":"min-h-screen bg-[#0a0a0a]","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"border-b border-[#1e1e1e] px-6 py-4","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-3xl mx-auto flex items-center justify-between","children":[["$","$L2",null,{"href":"/","className":"font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#c9a84c] hover:text-[#d4b660] transition-colors","children":"← Operators Brief"}],["$","a",null,{"href":"/#signup","className":"font-mono text-[11px] tracking-widest uppercase bg-[#c9a84c] text-[#0a0a0a] px-4 py-2 hover:bg-[#d4b660] transition-colors","children":"Get All 52 Issues — $15/mo"}]]}]}],["$","article",null,{"className":"max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-4 mb-8","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#c9a84c]","children":"Issue #01"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"w-1 h-1 bg-[#2a2a2a] rounded-full"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#5a5550]","children":"Free Sample"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"w-1 h-1 bg-[#2a2a2a] rounded-full"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#5a5550]","children":"March 4, 2026"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"w-1 h-1 bg-[#2a2a2a] rounded-full"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#5a5550]","children":"8-min read"}]]}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-[32px] md:text-[44px] font-light leading-[1.1] tracking-tight text-[#f0ede8] mb-5","children":"How One CPA Firm 3x'd Revenue Per Partner Without Hiring"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[18px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed mb-12 border-l-2 border-[#c9a84c] pl-5","children":"A mid-size accounting firm was drowning in reporting overhead. Here's the exact workflow they built, what it cost, and the numbers that came out the other side."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"w-full h-px bg-[#1e1e1e] mb-12"}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-14","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-3 mb-5","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#c9a84c]","children":"01"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#5a5550]","children":"The Problem"}]]}],["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-[24px] font-light text-[#f0ede8] mb-5 leading-snug","children":"320 hours a month disappearing into reporting"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[15px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed mb-4","children":"Client reporting was eating 8 hours per client per month. At 40 clients, that's 320 hours. That's 2 full-time employees worth of time — except it wasn't coming from employees. It was coming from partners."}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[15px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed mb-4","children":"The firm (based in Austin, TX — 6 partners, 40 business clients averaging $2,800/month) had a simple problem with a compounding cost: every monthly reporting cycle required pulling data from QuickBooks, normalizing it, writing a narrative summary, and packaging it into a branded PDF. Every. Single. Month. Per client."}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[15px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed mb-4","children":"Partners were spending 3–4 hours per client on work that was identical month over month. Meanwhile, advisory work — the kind clients actually pay premium for — was getting squeezed into whatever was left."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-[#0d0d0d] border border-[#1e1e1e] p-5 my-8","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[13px] font-mono text-[#5a5550] mb-2 uppercase tracking-wider","children":"The real cost calculation:"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[15px] text-[#f0ede8]","children":["40 clients × 8 hrs/month = 320 hrs",["$","br",null,{}],"320 hrs × $250 partner billing rate = ",["$","span",null,{"className":"text-[#c9a84c]","children":"$$80,000/month in unrecoverable time"}]]}]]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[15px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed","children":"They weren't losing money on reporting. They just weren't making any either — and they were too busy doing it to add clients."}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-14","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-3 mb-5","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#c9a84c]","children":"02"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#5a5550]","children":"The Workflow"}]]}],["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-[24px] font-light text-[#f0ede8] mb-5 leading-snug","children":"The 4-step system they built in 11 days"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[15px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed mb-8","children":"They didn't hire a developer. One partner with basic Zapier experience set this up across two weekends."}],[["$","div","0",{"className":"mb-6 border border-[#1e1e1e] bg-[#0d0d0d]","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"border-b border-[#1e1e1e] px-5 py-3 flex items-center justify-between","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#c9a84c] uppercase tracking-wider","children":"Step 1"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#5a5550] uppercase tracking-wider","children":"Zapier + QuickBooks Online"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"px-5 py-4","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-[15px] font-medium text-[#f0ede8] mb-3","children":"QuickBooks → Google Sheets (automated export)"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[13px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed","children":"Every 1st of the month, a Zap pulls the P&L, balance sheet, and cash flow statement for each client into a standardized Google Sheet template. The trigger is a scheduled Zap; the action maps QB line items to named sheet cells. Setup time: ~3 hours total across 40 clients using a bulk Zap template. Monthly maintenance: 0."}]]}]]}],["$","div","1",{"className":"mb-6 border border-[#1e1e1e] bg-[#0d0d0d]","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"border-b border-[#1e1e1e] px-5 py-3 flex items-center justify-between","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#c9a84c] uppercase tracking-wider","children":"Step 2"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#5a5550] uppercase tracking-wider","children":"Google Apps Script (free)"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"px-5 py-4","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-[15px] font-medium text-[#f0ede8] mb-3","children":"Google Sheets → structured JSON payload"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[13px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed","children":"A 40-line Apps Script reads the normalized sheet and outputs a JSON object: client name, reporting month, key metrics (revenue, expenses, net, YoY delta, top 3 expense categories, cash position). This JSON is what gets sent to Claude. Script runs automatically after the Zap completes."}]]}]]}],["$","div","2",{"className":"mb-6 border border-[#1e1e1e] bg-[#0d0d0d]","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"border-b border-[#1e1e1e] px-5 py-3 flex items-center justify-between","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#c9a84c] uppercase tracking-wider","children":"Step 3"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#5a5550] uppercase tracking-wider","children":"Claude API (claude-3-5-sonnet)"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"px-5 py-4","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-[15px] font-medium text-[#f0ede8] mb-3","children":"JSON → narrative report via Claude API"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[13px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed","children":"The JSON payload is sent to Claude with a firm-specific system prompt (see Section 05 below). Claude returns a structured narrative: executive summary, 3 key observations, one risk flag if applicable, one advisory prompt question. Output is plain text, pre-formatted for insertion into the PDF template. API cost per report: ~$0.04."}]]}]]}],["$","div","3",{"className":"mb-6 border border-[#1e1e1e] bg-[#0d0d0d]","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"border-b border-[#1e1e1e] px-5 py-3 flex items-center justify-between","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#c9a84c] uppercase tracking-wider","children":"Step 4"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#5a5550] uppercase tracking-wider","children":"Google Docs API + Gmail"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"px-5 py-4","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-[15px] font-medium text-[#f0ede8] mb-3","children":"Narrative → branded PDF → client email"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[13px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed","children":"The narrative drops into a Google Doc template (firm logo, colors, standard layout). Google Docs API exports as PDF. Gmail sends it to the client contact with a subject line generated by Claude: \"[Client Name] — [Month] Financial Brief: [One-line insight]\". Total end-to-end time per client: 4 minutes. Human review: 15 minutes for all 40 clients combined."}]]}]]}]]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-14","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-3 mb-5","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#c9a84c]","children":"03"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#5a5550]","children":"The Numbers"}]]}],["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-[24px] font-light text-[#f0ede8] mb-5 leading-snug","children":"Before and after, in cold hard numbers"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[15px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed mb-8","children":"These are actuals from mon